{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/DSimp/App.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.DSimp.dsimpAppArgs\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">DSimp</span>.<span class=\"name\">dsimpAppArgs</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/DSimp/DSimpM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.DSimp.DSimpM\">DSimpM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/DSimp/DSimpM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.DSimp.Result\">Result</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Walks the application spine and `dsimp`s each argument unless `ProofInstInfo` marks it\nas a proof or instance. The function head itself is not recursively simplified — atomic\nheads (`.const`, `.fvar`) are no-ops anyway, and complex heads can be handled by\nuser-supplied `pre`/`post` simprocs.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/DSimp/App.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.DSimp.dsimpAppArgs","kind":"def","line":35,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.DSimp.dsimpAppArgs","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/DSimp/App.lean#L35-L67"}}],"imports":["Init.Omega","Lean.Meta.Sym.AlphaShareBuilder","Lean.Meta.Sym.DSimp.DSimpM","Lean.Meta.Sym.DSimp.Result","Lean.Meta.Sym.ProofInstInfo"],"instances":[],"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.DSimp.App"}